tool.name: MapTreemaps

param.name: out_fc
param.dialogReference: The output feature class that will be created and to which the results will be written.
param.pythonReference: The output feature class that will be created and to which the results will be written.

param.name: value
param.dialogReference: Specifies the numeric field containing the attribute values that will be used to apportion the area of each segment of the treemap and the size of the proportional treemap symbols. Null values are excluded from the calculations.
param.pythonReference: Specifies the numeric field containing the attribute values that will be used to apportion the area of each segment of the treemap and the size of the proportional treemap symbols. Null values are excluded from the calculations.

param.name: group_field
param.dialogReference:
The field in the input that will be used to geographically aggregate features. Features within each group will have their coordinates averaged to determine the centroid of the treemap symbol and the sum of the numeric values within the group will determine the scaling of the proportional treemap symbol.

Suggested values might included administrative areas such as, neighborhoods, states/provinces, and countries.
param.pythonReference:
The field in the input that will be used to geographically aggregate features. Features within each group will have their coordinates averaged to determine the centroid of the treemap symbol and the sum of the numeric values within the group will determine the scaling of the proportional treemap symbol.

Suggested values might included administrative areas such as, neighborhoods, states/provinces, and countries.

param.name: category_field
param.dialogReference: The field in the input that will be used to apportion segments with each treemap symbol. Features with common category values will be aggregated.
param.pythonReference: The field in the input that will be used to apportion segments with each treemap symbol. Features with common category values will be aggregated.

param.name: width_min
param.dialogReference:
A numerical constraint that will be used to determine the minimum proportional treemap symbol width. The area of the treemap symbols will be scaled proportionally based on the aggregated data values within the group.

This measurement uses the units of the input feature coordinate system and may require some experimentation to achieve the desired effect.
param.pythonReference:

This measurement uses the units of the input feature coordinate system and may require some experimentation to achieve the desired effect.

param.name: width_max
param.dialogReference:
A numerical constraint that will be used to determine the maximum proportional treemap symbol width. The area of the treemap symbols will be scaled proportionally based on the aggregated data values within the group.

This measurement uses the units of the input feature coordinate system and may require some experimentation to achieve the desired effect.

tool.summary: Geoprocessing tool for aggregating features into proportional treemaps on a map.
